Start-up and Process Launch Tools

roscore
The basis nodes and programs for ROS-based systems.  
A roscore must be running for ROS nodes to communicate.
Usage:
$ roscore
 
rosrun
Runs a ROS packageâ€™s executable with minimal typing.
Usage:
$ rosrun packagename executablename
Example (runs turtlesim):$ rosrun turtlesim turtlesimnode

roslaunch
Starts a roscore (if needed), local nodes, remote nodes viaSSH, and sets parameter server parameters.
Examples:
Launch a file in a package:
$ roslaunch packagename filename.launch
Launch on a different port:
$ roslaunch -p 1234 packagename filename.launch
Launch on the local nodes:
$ roslaunch --local packagename filename.launch


